The paper discusses a technique for spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which falls under the category of wireless communication and networking. Specifically, the paper focuses on energy-efficient sensing techniques, which suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the control of interference and false alarm rates, which suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and cognitive radio (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a method for optimizing sensing parameters, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
